caption: I always ordered from this place because its the closest to me. The lady who takes the orders over the phone and in store was extremely rude to me. She didn't even let me finish telling her my order. When I went in to pick up my order I kindly told her how I felt uncomfortable the way she spoke on the phone. Her response was "if you felt any type of way that's your problem I'm busy". And I let her know that's not okay I work in a customer service job and I would never speak to any customer that way. But she didn't care and proceeded to ask me if I want the food or not continuously. I refuse to take the food because the way she handled it was unprofessional. I will not be coming here again.

Rude customer service over the phone to make an order. These kind of businesses survive only because you have customers like us. But if you treat customers with attitudes, how you expect us to order from you? Will not be ordering again from here.

I eat here about twice a year. I either eat in or order delivery. Either way food is fresh & delivery time is good. They are straight up & polite. Now you can order through grub hub, order plain/supreme burritos (with/without rice) & there’s a $2 delivery fee. Make sure you read the ingredients because the rice & beans in a burrito are the ingredients that balance out the meats acidity. Most importantly deliveries stop at 6pm.
